     <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Alias_identification_arm  Type: alias_identification_item 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Alias_identification_arm.alias_identification_item">
The <b>alias_identification_item</b> type is an extensible list of alternate data types. It provides a mechanism to refer to instances of the data types included in the types that extend the <b>alias_identification_item</b> type. 
<note number="1">
This empty extensible select requires extension in a further module to ensure that all entities have at least one valid instantiation. 
</note>

<note number="2">The type <b>alias_identification_item</b> is not an extension of the type <express_ref linkend="identification_assignment:mim:Identification_assignment_mim.identification_item"/>, defined in the application module <module_ref linkend="identification_assignment:introduction"/>, because 
the capability to get an alias may not be needed for every entity type to which the capability to get additional identifiers is provided.
By nature, <b>alias_identification_item</b> characterizes a smaller set of entity types than <express_ref linkend="identification_assignment:mim:Identification_assignment_mim.identification_item"/>.
</note>
</ext_description>
  <!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Alias_identification_arm  Entity: Alias_identification 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Alias_identification_arm.Alias_identification">
An <b>Alias_identification</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="identification_assignment:arm:Identification_assignment_arm.Identification_assignment"/>

 that provides an alias identifier to product or activity data.
<note number="1">The alias identifier is conveyed within the identifier attribute inherited from <express_ref linkend="identification_assignment:arm:Identification_assignment_arm.Identification_assignment"/>.
</note>
<note number="2">Information about the organizational scope in which the alias applies may be provided by a specialization of <express_ref linkend="person_organization_assignment:arm:Person_organization_assignment_arm.Organization_or_person_in_organization_assignment"/>.
</note>
<note number="3">Alias identification only applies to concepts that possesses an attribute that conveys an identifier.
</note>

</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Alias_identification_arm  Entity: Alias_identification  Attribute: role 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->

   <ext_description linkend="Alias_identification_arm.Alias_identification.role">
 the inherited attribute <express_ref linkend="identification_assignment:arm:Identification_assignment_arm.Identification_assignment.role"/>. The value of <express_ref linkend="identification_assignment:arm:Identification_assignment_arm.Identification_assignment.role"/>

 shall be  'alias';
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
